OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
STUNNING GRAB FROM JAISWAL Akash Deep bowling to Zakir Hasan, good length ball, pitching outside off stump, Zakir Hasan steps down and swings hoping to break his duck but the leather kisses the willow's edge and goes towards the gully. Jaiswal dives low to his right, scooping up a beauty. The umpires check the catch, and after multiple replays, it’s confirmed as clean—OUT! India strikes early, with Zakir falling for a 24-ball duck.

OverHistory.NewCommentry: Akash Deep to Shadman Islam Wicket
OverHistory.Commentry: Akash Deep bowling to Shadman Islam, short of good length ball, pitching on off stump, Shadman Islam plays a defensive shot on back foot WICKET Shadman Islam lbw Akash Deep (Bangladesh 29 Runs for 2 wickets), Appeal from the fielding side
OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
EXCELLENT REVIEW FROM INDIA! Akash Deep bowling to Shadman Islam, short of good length ball, pitching on off stump, Shadman Islam stuck on the crease, misjudged the line as the ball angled in and missed his defence completely, striking him on the pads.Big appeal turned down, but Akash Deep is adamant and convinces Rohit to review. The replay shows three reds—what a call! Rohit, surprised and elated, credits Akash Deep for the perfect review. Both openers are now back in the pavilion 

WICKET Shadman Islam lbw Akash Deep (Bangladesh 29 Runs for 2 wickets)

???? When the giant screen showed three Reds ???

Akash Deep gets his second courtesy of a successful DRS!

Bangladesh move to 74/2 after 26 overs.

Stay tuned for the afternoon session ?

Scorecard - https://t.co/JBVX2gyyPf#TeamIndia | #INDvBAN | @IDFCFIRSTBank pic.twitter.com/Jocxs8Ld9p

— BCCI (@BCCI) September 27, 2024

Lunch on day one has been an intriguing session with the game finely poised. India’s bowlers, led by Bumrah and Siraj, found movement early, but it was Akash Deep who made the breakthroughs, removing both openers. The ground is being covered as the Drizzle has increased. India will be eager to shake things up after lunch. Session 2 Will start at 1:25 PM IST.

OverHistory.Commentry: Ravichandran Ashwin bowling to Najmul Hossain Shanto, full length ball, pitching outside off stump, Najmul Hossain Shanto plays a forward defensive shot WICKET Najmul Hossain Shanto lbw Ravichandran Ashwin (Bangladesh 80 Runs for 3 wickets), Appeal from the fielding side
OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
PLUMB IN FRONT AND ASH BREAKS THE PARTNERSHIP Ravichandran Ashwin bowling to Najmul Hossain Shanto, full-length ball, pitching outside off stump, Najmul Hossain Shanto plays for turn that isn’t there, and he’s struck plumb in front.Big shout for LBW and Umpire  barely has time to blink before his finger’s up. Shanto instantly reviews, but it’s wishful thinking—three reds, bang on target. Even Shubman’s flashy dive at second slip won’t save the Bangladesh skipper from losing both his wicket and a review. India celebrates as Ashwin breaks the partnership in style!

WICKET Najmul Hossain Shanto lbw Ravichandran Ashwin (Bangladesh 80 Runs for 3 wickets)

The opening day of the second Test in Kanpur has been cut short due to persistent rain, with only 35 overs bowled. Bangladesh finished at 107/3, with Shanto and Mominul steadying the innings after Akash Deep's double strike and Ashwin's key dismissal. Play will resume at 9.30 AM on Day 2.

STUNNER FROM HITMAN! Mohammed Siraj bowling to Litton Das, good length ball, pitching outside off stump, Litton Das charging down the wicket, tries to swing up and over but mistimes the connection. The ball rockets towards wide mid-off, Hit in the air and Rohit pulls off an absolute blinder! with perfect timing, leaps up and snatches it one-handed! The Indian skipper is off running in celebration, leaving his teammates and everyone in awe. What a catch—pure brilliance from Rohit! 

WICKET Litton Das c Rohit Sharma b Mohammed Siraj (Bangladesh 148 Runs for 5 wickets)

OverHistory.NewCommentry: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shakib Al Hasan Wicket
OverHistory.Commentry: Ravichandran Ashwin bowling to Shakib Al Hasan, full length ball, pitching on off stump, Shakib Al Hasan steps down and plays an aggressive lofted off drive WICKET Shakib Al Hasan c Mohammed Siraj b Ravichandran Ashwin (Bangladesh 170 Runs for 6 wickets) towards Long-Off
OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
UP, UP... AND SIRAJ PULLS OFF AN ABSOLUTE BLINDER! Ravichandran Ashwin bowling to Shakib Al Hasan, full length ball, pitching on off stump, Shakib Al Hasan charges down, swings with everything he's got and the ball rockets into the stratosphere! Siraj at mid-off turns on the jets, sprinting back with unwavering focus. He dives full stretch, snatches it over his shoulder while tumbling backwards, and holds on to a one-handed stunner! The stadium is in an absolute frenzy! Teammates are losing their minds, and Shakib can't believe his eyes. Siraj has just pulled a rabbit out of the hat—that's a catch for the highlight reels! 

WICKET Shakib Al Hasan c Mohammed Siraj b Ravichandran Ashwin (Bangladesh 170 Runs for 6 wickets)

Another outstanding catch and this time it is @mdsirajofficial who picks up a tough one to dismiss Shakib Al Hasan.

Live - https://t.co/JBVX2gyyPf… #INDvBAN@IDFCFIRSTBank pic.twitter.com/RbKZKDdGAW

— BCCI (@BCCI) September 30, 2024

OverHistory.NewCommentry: Ravichandran Ashwin to Zakir Hasan Wicket
OverHistory.Commentry: Ravichandran Ashwin bowling to Zakir Hasan, full length ball, pitching on leg stump, Zakir Hasan plays a forward defensive shot WICKET Zakir Hasan lbw Ravichandran Ashwin (Bangladesh 18 Runs for 1 wickets), Appeal from the fielding side
OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
A TOUCH OF MAGIC FROM ASH Ravichandran Ashwin bowling to Zakir Hasan, full length ball, pitching on leg stump, Zakir Hasan lighted delivery from around the wicket, pitching middle-leg, turns away sharply. Zakir's forward defense found wanting, beaten by turn and bounce.Impact on back thigh, plumb in front. DRS confirms: three reds on ball-tracking. Textbook off-break from Ashwin, exploiting conditions expertly.India draws first blood. Ashwin's guile proves decisive, setting the tone for potential final innings drama. 
 

WICKET Zakir Hasan lbw Ravichandran Ashwin (Bangladesh 18 Runs for 1 wickets)

OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
TIMBER ALERT ft.JADDU Ravindra Jadeja bowling to Najmul Hossain Shanto, good length ball, pitching outside leg stump, Najmul Hossain Shanto lunges forward for an audacious reverse sweep. Fatal error! He exposes his leg stump, not to the pitch, and misjudges the turn. The ball kisses the top edge and demolishes the woodwork.

WICKET Najmul Hossain Shanto b Ravindra Jadeja (Bangladesh 91 Runs for 4 wickets)

That's the breakthrough!

A beautiful delivery by @imjadeja as the Bangladesh Captain is bowled out.
